{
  "text": "a) The effect of laser irradiation on oxidative metabolism of cells as evaluated by chemoluminescence measurements. b) The ability of laser light-stimulated cells to incorporate tritiated thymidine as an indication of DNA synthesis. [CITATION_1] The use of these precise biological tools are now revealing that wavelength-specific laser energy can modulate tissue repair and wound healing.",
